title: Mimir
message: >-
  If you reference Mimir in academic or technical work, please cite it using
  the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Alain
    family-names: Dormehl
    email: alaindormehl@gmail.com
    affiliation: Build Epic Shit Studios
repository-code: 'https://github.com/buildepicshit/Mimir'
url: 'https://github.com/buildepicshit/Mimir'
abstract: >-
  An experimental multi-agent memory governance/control plane. Canonical
  storage uses an agent-native bytecode-like intermediate representation;
  librarian-mediated single-writer writes with compiler-style validation;
  bi-temporal append-only storage with stable symbol tracking;
  grounding-aware deterministic confidence decay; checkpoint-triggered
  episode atomicity; DAG supersession; scoped promotion with provenance; and
  consensus-quorum evidence drafts that preserve dissent instead of treating
  model agreement as truth.
keywords:
  - agent-memory
  - multi-agent-systems
  - memory-governance
  - scoped-memory
  - consensus-quorum
  - compiler-architecture
  - bi-temporal-store
  - symbol-tracking
  - llm-tooling
